00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:12.000
 Hamamelis virginiana is a natural shrub of North America (Nebraska, Virginia, Texas and Florida) 

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:20.000
 It grows in humid or boggy forests of temperate areas. 

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:28.000
 It is 2-7 meters high, with the spongy bark of gray, similar to the hazelnut. 

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:35.000
 The leaves are alternate, with short petioles that fall before blooming. 

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:43.000
 The flowers appear in winter in groups of 3 or 4. 

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:50.000
 It has small chalice and four yellow petals. 

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:57.000
 The fruit is a hazelnut shaped capsule that contains the seeds. 

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:04.000
 Its composition consists of: Tannins, flavonoids, saponins, sugars and essential oils. 

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:11.000
 The richness in tannins and flavonoids provides astringent, antiseptic, anti-inflammatory and hemostatic properties. 

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:20.000
 Traditionally it was used by Native Americans to cure wounds, treatment of tumors or joint pain. 

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:27.000
 Astringent properties act on the circulatory system to solve problems such as hemorrhoids, varicose veins, phlebitis, bruises, ... 

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:34.000
 Witch hazel is used in cosmetics for the skin, for the development of mixed skin creams, sun-burns, urticaria. 

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:41.000
 It has been proven that the use of this plant helps to reduce the bumps produced by menopause. 

00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:50.000
 It is a good anti-inflammatory, it has analgesic properties useful in the treatment of sprains, luxation and distension. 

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:58.000
 It is used in the treatment for angina because it has antibiotic properties. 

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:05.000
 In the case of toxicity, the external use of this plant is considered to be safe, but at the internal level, precautions must be taken. 

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:12.000
 The plant is rich in safrole that can induce the formation of cancer cells. Long treatments are contraindicated. 

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:19.000
 Its internal use is contraindicated during pregnancy and breastfeeding. 

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:26.000
 Hammelis when it is very tannin-rich can cause stomach or intestinal adverse reactions. 

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:34.000
 Homemade remedies can be made with this plant, such as hemorrhoid witch hazel. 

